e15p7aqh1"><span class="css-1b6omqv esbq1260"><span>&amp;nbsp;</span></span></div></div><div id="jobDescriptionTitle"><h2 tabindex="-1" id="jobDescriptionTitleHeading" class="css-wpzt8u e1tiznh50">Full job description</h2></div><div id="jobDescriptionText" class="jobsearch-JobComponent-description css-16y4thd eu4oa1w0"><p><b>About Us:</b></p>
<p>Founded in 2013, Porch Software has become an industry leader in the Fintech arena. We doubled in size in 2024 and continue to project unprecedented growth through 2025 and beyond. With such rapid expansion comes the need to quickly hire motivated and experienced developers to balance out our teams and get iterations to market faster. Our core customers are Fortune 300 companies. You would be joining an organization with a true “created-in-a-garage” story, the founders have been here since day one. As such, our culture reflects one of self-reliance, drive, and dedication.</p>
<p><b>Job Description:</b></p>
<p>We are seeking a skilled and experienced Fullstack Developer to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in VueJs, Javascript and .NET Core, with a minimum of 3 years of hands-on experience in developing high-traffic platforms.</p>
<p><b>Responsibilities:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Develop and maintain web applications using JavaScript and Vue.js for the front end.</li>
<li>Design and implement backend services and APIs using ASP.NET and .NET Core.</li>
<li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define, design, and ship new features.</li>
<li>Ensure the performance, quality, and responsiveness of applications.</li>
<li>Identify and correct bottlenecks and fix bugs.</li>
<li>Help maintain code quality, organization, and automation.</li>
<li>Stay up-to-date with emerging technologies and industry trends.</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Requirements:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Minimum of 3 years of professional experience as a Full Stack Developer.</li>
<li>Strong proficiency in JavaScript and experience with Vue.js.</li>
<li>Solid understanding of ASP.NET and .NET Core.</li>
<li>Experience with RESTful APIs and web services.</li>
<li>Familiarity with database technologies such as SQL Server or MySQL.</li>
<li>Knowledge of version control systems, such as Git.</li>
<li>Excellent problem-solving skills and attention to detail.</li>
<li>Strong communication and teamwork abilities.</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Preferred Qualifications:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Experience with other front-end frameworks like React or Angular.</li>
<li>Understanding of DevOps practices and CI/CD pipelines.</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Benefits:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Competitive salary and benefits package.</li>
<li>Opportunities for professional growth and development.</li>
<li>Collaborative and inclusive work environment.</li>
<li>Flexible working hours and remote work options.</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Work Remotely:</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Yes</li>
<li>Unfortunately, we cannot accept applicants from CA or NY at this time.</li>
<li>Visa sponsorship is not available for this job.</li>
</ul>
<p>Porch Software does not discriminate in employment on the basis of race, color, religion, sex (including pregnancy and gender identity), national origin, political affiliation, sexual orientation, marital status, disability, genetic information, age, membership in an employee organization, retaliation, parental status, military service, or other non-merit factor.</p>
<p>Job Type: Full-time</p>
<p>Pay: $80,000.00 - $120,000.00 per year</p>
<p>Experience:</p>
<ul>
<li>Full-stack development: 4 years (Required)</li>
</ul>
